The ewceData package is a **data-experiment** package and 
data-experiment packages are only built and propagated 3 times a week 
(Tue, Wed, Fri). Turns out that they ran today and this allowed ewceData 
to propagate to our public package repos for the first time:

   - Today's build results:
 
https://master.bioconductor.org/checkResults/3.13/data-experiment-LATEST/ewceData/

   - Landing page:
       https://bioconductor.org/packages/3.13/ewceData

Now that ewceData propagated, the build machines running the 
**software** builds will be able to install it, and this in turn will 
make it possible for them to install EWCE. This should be reflected on 
tomorrow's report.

Finally note that the fact that riesling1 was actually able to bypass 
all these steps and get ewceData before the other builders is because 
this machine also happens to run the data-experiment builds in addition 
to the software builds.

Cheers,
H.


